fields.portfolio_description:
The M&M’s Pixit App was built for M&M’s/Mars Corporation. It was a photo booth app that allowed M&M’s photographers to take pictures of customers at the M&M’s World store in New York city. Once the picture was taken and a customer survey was completed. The app sent the picture and data to a web server which then posted the picture on the giant big screen outside the M&M’s World store in NYC.

The M&M’s Pixit App was built to run on Apple IOS and Android using Apache Cordova framework. Similar to PhoneGap, Apache Cordova is an open source distributed framework.
